'''A̱bwom a̱byin''':  

A̱byin '''Zi̱mbabwe''', á̱ lyen ma̱ng a̱lyoot a̱gwomna̱ti nka nang '''Ri̱pobi̱lik Zimbabwe''' wu, yet a̱byin kya nang bibyin ghyáng keang di̱ tityak a̱ni ka̱ shyia̱ di̱ fam-a̱byin A̱tak Afrika, tsi̱tsak a̱ka̱ghyui Zambezi ma̱ng Limpopo na, ka̱ si̱ byia̱ a̱gi̱gak ma̱ng bibyin [[Afrika A̱tak]] di̱ fam a̱tak hu, [[Botswana]] di̱ fam a̱tak-jenshyung hu, [[Zambya]] di̱ fam a̱za hu, mbeang [[Mozambik]] di̱ fam a̱tyin hu. A̱keangtung nka ka̱ ka ngyet a̱gba̱ndang a̱keang nka a̱ swak ma̱ng shi a̱ni kya yet Harare. A̱gba̱ndang a̱keang a̱feang wu wa yet Bulawayo. A̱byin ka si̱ byia̱ á̱niet ba̱ na ntat miliyon 15 a̱ni,<ref name=macro/> Zimbabwe byia̱ lilyem a̱gwomna̱ti 16,<ref name="language" /> ma̱ng [[Shong (a̱lyem)|Shong]], Shona, mbeang Ndebele nang lilyem á̱niet ma̱ a̱di̱di̱t hu. Á̱ ku yorong "A̱sham A̱na Afrika" (Shong: "Jewel of Afrika") mat a̱dodo ya a̱son nka wu di̱n jen a̱ja.<ref>Boris, Johnson (15 Zwat Swak ma̱ng Jhyiung 2017). [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/15/robert-mugabe-tarnished-jewel-zimbabwe-now-chance-shine/ Robert Mugabe tarnished the jewel that is Zimbabwe. Now is its chance to shine again] (di̱n Shong). The Telegraph. www.telegraph.co.uk </ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.nybooks.com/articles/2003/04/10/the-jewel-of-africa/|title=The Jewel of Africa|first=Doris|last=Lessing|date=10 April 2003|via=www.nybooks.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.voazimbabwe.com/a/zimbabwe-economy-battered-over-the-years/2724325.html|title=What Happened to Zimbabwe, Once Known as The Jewel of Africa?|first=Irwin|last=Chifera}}</ref>

